  "text": "SRM can be regarded as a region growing and merging technique, since it first checks if two neighbouring pixels belong to the same segment and then merges the pixels if a pre-defined criteria is satisfied [CITATION_1] . To this end, a set of neighbouring pixel pairs are prepared. Using a sort function, the 3164  2765  2920  2  4931  5004  4890  4920  3  58214  63209  56763  62331  4  10524  11223  12339  13402  5  4654  5198  4590  5060  6  7088  5345  6980  5205  7  1290  2790  1243  2646  8  2779  2635  2734  2540  9  14056  15011  13504  13902  10  25021  32146  22344  30243 couples of pixels are then sorted in an ascending order using the following function, where p and p' are a given pixel and its neighbor, respectively 20 :",
